            {% render 'pf-4fbeb370' %}
            {% endif %}</div><div data-section-id="pf-14da" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dBFCZX khzvmY pf-12_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gvPcJq dRaLso"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-13_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-14_"><h1 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-15_ pf-heading-1-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-17_">What is the role of the Care Quality Commission?</span></h1><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-role-of-the-care-quality-commission--dr--richard-dune--1676449178596.png?v=1676449194" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-role-of-the-care-quality-commission--dr--richard-dune--1676449178596.png?v=1676449194 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-role-of-the-care-quality-commission--dr--richard-dune--1676449178596_1000x.png?v=1676449194 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-role-of-the-care-quality-commission--dr--richard-dune--1676449178596_500x.png?v=1676449194 320w" width="3500" height="2333" alt="What is the role of the Care Quality Commission? - Dr Richard Dune -" title="What is the role of the Care Quality Commission? - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-18_ pf-image-1"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-4c12" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dBFCZX khzvmY pf-19_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gvPcJq dRaLso"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-20_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-21_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-22_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-24_">Undoubtedly, the UK's health and social care sectors are among the most heavily regulated worldwide. A legal duty of care is placed on service providers by law as they provide services to the public.<br><br>In this article, <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/dr-richard-dune-blog" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(0, 71, 178);"><i>Dr Richard Dune</i></span></a> presents an overview of the role and responsibilities of the Care Quality Commission (CQC). In addition, he will describe the services that are regulated by the CQC, including those that require cross-sector inspections.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-25_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-27_">What is the role of the Care Quality Commission?</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-role-of-the-care-quality-commission--dr-richard-dune--1676635621132.png?v=1676635628" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-role-of-the-care-quality-commission--dr-richard-dune--1676635621132.png?v=1676635628 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-role-of-the-care-quality-commission--dr-richard-dune--1676635621132_500x.png?v=1676635628 320w" width="3890" height="3456" alt="What is the role of the Care Quality Commission? - Dr Richard Dune -" title="What is the role of the Care Quality Commission? - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-28_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-29_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-31_">The <span style="color: rgb(0, 71, 178);"></span>Care Quality Commission<i><span></span></i> (CQC) is England's independent regulator of health and social care services. It was established in 2009 as a non-departmental public executive body sponsored by the Department of Health and Social Care.<br><br>Its primary mandate is to ensure the quality and safety of care services in hospitals, dentists, ambulances, and care homes and the care given in people's homes.<br><br>The CQC is responsible for the following:
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-djVWQC gSkqPQ pf-32_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-33_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-35_">Registering health and care providers in England</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-36_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-38_">Inspecting, rating, and monitoring the quality of health and social care services</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-39_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-41_">Ensuring that people who use services are protected
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-42_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-44_">Contributing to the debate on major issues of quality in health and social care with an independent voice.
</span></li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-45_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-47_">Extended role of the CQC</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/extended-role-of-the-cqc--richard-dune-phd--1676447666807.png?v=1676447679" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/extended-role-of-the-cqc--richard-dune-phd--1676447666807.png?v=1676447679 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/extended-role-of-the-cqc--richard-dune-phd--1676447666807_500x.png?v=1676447679 320w" width="3700" height="2467" alt="Extended role of the CQC - What is the extended role of the CQC? - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Extended role of the CQC - What is the extended role of the CQC? - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-48_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-49_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-51_">As part of their work, CQC also:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-djVWQC gSkqPQ pf-52_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-53_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-55_">Ensures that the rights of vulnerable individuals, including those subject to restrictions under the Mental Health Act, are protected</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-56_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-58_">Pays attention to what people say about health and social care services and takes appropriate action</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-59_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-61_">Engages the public and those receiving care in the process
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-62_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-64_">Collaborates with other organisations and public groups.
</span></li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-65_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-67_">History of the CQC</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/history-of-the-cqc--richard-dune-phd--1676447841191.png?v=1676447853" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/history-of-the-cqc--richard-dune-phd--1676447841191.png?v=1676447853 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/history-of-the-cqc--richard-dune-phd--1676447841191_500x.png?v=1676447853 320w" width="3700" height="2598" alt="History of the CQC - What is the history of the CQC? - Dr Richard Dune -" title="History of the CQC - What is the history of the CQC? - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-68_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-69_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-71_">The CQC was founded in 2009, following the dissolution of the following three predecessor organisations:
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-djVWQC gSkqPQ pf-72_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-73_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-75_">The Healthcare Commission
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-76_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-78_">The Commission for Social Care Inspection
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-79_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-81_">The Mental Health Act Commission.
</span></li></ul><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-82_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-84_">The Healthcare Commission and Commission for Social Care Inspection regulated health and adult social care in England until 31 March 2009, while the Mental Health Act Commission monitored the operation of the Mental Health Act 1983.<br><br>The Health and Social Care Act 2008 established the CQC as a single, integrated regulator for England's health and adult social care services. An interim commission was established on 1 October 2008 and commenced operations on 1 April 2009.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-85_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-87_">What is the purpose of CQC?</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/which-type-of-services-does-cqc-regulate--richard-dune-phd--1676448662572.png?v=1676448682" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/which-type-of-services-does-cqc-regulate--richard-dune-phd--1676448662572.png?v=1676448682 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/which-type-of-services-does-cqc-regulate--richard-dune-phd--1676448662572_500x.png?v=1676448682 320w" width="1800" height="1506" alt="What is the purpose of CQC? - Dr Richard Dune -" title="What is the purpose of CQC? - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-88_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-89_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-91_">As a regulator of health and social care services, the CQC ensures that people receive safe, effective, compassionate, and high-quality care. It encourages service providers to improve their services as necessary.<br><br>In addition to conducting checks during the registration process for all new care services, the CQC also monitors a wide variety of data sources that may indicate problems in the service. One of the commission's responsibilities is to protect the interests of people whose rights have been restricted under the Mental Health Act.<br>
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-92_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-94_">What are the CQC core values?</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-are-the-cqc-core-values--richard-dune-phd--1676448572048.png?v=1676448619" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-are-the-cqc-core-values--richard-dune-phd--1676448572048.png?v=1676448619 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-are-the-cqc-core-values--richard-dune-phd--1676448572048_500x.png?v=1676448619 320w" width="3500" height="2626" alt="What are the CQC core values? - Dr Richard Dune -" title="What are the CQC core values? - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-95_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-96_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-98_">The four values of the CQC are:
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-djVWQC gSkqPQ pf-99_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-100_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-102_"><b>Excellence</b> - Being a high-performing organisation is the hallmark of excellence
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-103_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-105_"><b>Caring</b> - Respect and dignity are integral components of caring for others
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-106_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-108_"><b>Integrity</b> - Doing the right thing every time is what integrity is all about

</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-109_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-111_"><b>Teamwork</b> - As a team, we must learn from each other to be the best we can be.
</span></li></ul><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-112_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-114_">Which type of services does CQC regulate?</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-purpose-of-cqc--dr-richard-dune--1676464900072.png?v=1676464907" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-purpose-of-cqc--dr-richard-dune--1676464900072.png?v=1676464907 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/what-is-the-purpose-of-cqc--dr-richard-dune--1676464900072_500x.png?v=1676464907 320w" width="2500" height="1656" alt="Which type of services does CQC regulate? - Dr Richard Dune -" title="Which type of services does CQC regulate? - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-115_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-116_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-118_">CQC regulates the following health and social care services in England:
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-djVWQC gSkqPQ pf-119_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-120_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-122_"><b>Ambulances</b> - Both NHS and independent ambulance services
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-123_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-125_"><b>Care homes</b> - Residential and nursing homes
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-126_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-128_"><b>Healthcare clinics</b> - Including family planning and slimming clinics

</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-129_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-131_"><b>Services in the community</b> - Community-based services, such as those for people with learning disabilities and those for substance abuse
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-132_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-134_"><b>Dental services</b> - NHS and independent dental services
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-135_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-137_"><b>GPs and primary care doctors</b> - GP practices, walk-in centres, and out-of-hours services
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-138_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-140_"><b>Hospices </b>- Hospices that provide care to patients with life-limiting conditions or near death
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-141_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-143_"><b>Hospitals</b> - Both NHS trusts and independent hospitals
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-144_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-146_"><b>Mental health</b> - NHS and independent mental health services for detained patients
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-147_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-149_"><b>Services in your home</b> - Including home care agencies, mobile doctors, and telephone-based services.
</span></li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-150_ pf-heading-1-h3 _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-152_">Cross-sector inspections
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/crosssector-inspections--conclusion--dr-richard-dune--1676447307146.png?v=1676447320" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/crosssector-inspections--conclusion--dr-richard-dune--1676447307146.png?v=1676447320 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/t/33/assets/crosssector-inspections--conclusion--dr-richard-dune--1676447307146_500x.png?v=1676447320 320w" width="3500" height="2333" alt="CQC cross-sector inspections - Dr Richard Dune -" title="CQC cross-sector inspections - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-153_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-154_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-156_">The CQC sometimes conducts joint inspections of services with other inspectorates, including system-wide inspections. A system inspection aims to assess a group of services in a local area. This way, CQC can examine how individual services are integrated to provide care across the entire system.<br><br>Cross-sector inspections carried out by CQC, and other inspectorates include:<br>
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-djVWQC gSkqPQ pf-157_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-158_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-160_"><b>Children's services</b> - All health services for children with the Office for Standards in Education, Children's Services and Skills (Ofsted) and service commissioners
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-161_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-163_"><b>Defence medical services</b> - Defence medical treatment facilities in conjunction with the Defence Medical Services Regulator (DMSR)
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-164_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-166_"><b>Secure settings</b> - Joint inspections with the HM Inspectorate of Prisons (HMIP) and other authorities

</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-epRwmx ilWFMI pf-167_ pf-text-1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-169_"><b>Urgent and emergency care systems</b> - Localised system-wide inspections across urgent and emergency care services.
